comment: RATR shows that Cole (NOP) and Anderson (NOP) maintain legal guarding position as they defend Clarkson's (LAL) driving layup attempt.
Randle (LAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Nance Jr. (LAL) makes contact with Evans' (NOP) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Holiday (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Williams' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (LAL) sets the screen on Holiday (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Anderson (NOP) makes contact with Williams' (LAL) arm at the start of his upward shooting motion that affects his jump shot attempt.
Gee (NOP) makes incidental contact with Randle (LAL) that does not affect his RSBQ on the drive to the basket.
Holiday (NOP) makes incidental body to body contact as he reaches in and deflects the ball away from Williams (LAL).
RHH shows that Anderson (NOP) legally contests Williams' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Evans (NOP) makes a legal move to create space from Clarkson (LAL).
Anderson (NOP) grabs Randle's (LAL) arm after he secures the rebound and causes him to lose control of the ball.
